{"schemaVersion":{"minor":3,"patch":0,"major":0},"metadata":{"roleHeading":"Type Method","symbolKind":"method","modules":[{"name":"PushwooshCore"}],"title":"setUser:emails:","fragments":[{"text":"+ ","kind":"text"},{"kind":"identifier","text":"setUser:emails:"}],"role":"symbol","externalID":"c:objc(pl)PWConfiguration(cm)setUser:emails:","navigatorTitle":[{"text":"setUser:emails:","kind":"identifier"}]},"abstract":[{"type":"text","text":"Sets user identifier and emails together in a single operation."}],"variants":[{"traits":[{"interfaceLanguage":"occ"}],"paths":["\/documentation\/pushwooshcore\/pwconfiguration\/setuser:emails:"]}],"primaryContentSections":[{"declarations":[{"tokens":[{"kind":"text","text":"+ ("},{"kind":"typeIdentifier","text":"void","preciseIdentifier":"c:v"},{"text":") ","kind":"text"},{"text":"setUser:","kind":"identifier"},{"text":"(","kind":"text"},{"text":"NSString","kind":"typeIdentifier","preciseIdentifier":"c:objc(cs)NSString"},{"kind":"text","text":" *) "},{"kind":"internalParam","text":"userId"},{"text":" ","kind":"text"},{"kind":"identifier","text":"emails:"},{"text":"(","kind":"text"},{"text":"NSArray","preciseIdentifier":"c:objc(cs)NSArray","kind":"typeIdentifier"},{"kind":"text","text":" *) "},{"kind":"internalParam","text":"emails"},{"kind":"text","text":";"}],"platforms":["iOS"],"languages":["occ"]}],"kind":"declarations"},{"kind":"parameters","parameters":[{"content":[{"inlineContent":[{"text":"The custom user identifier.","type":"text"}],"type":"paragraph"}],"name":"userId"},{"content":[{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"Array of email address strings to associate with the user."}]}],"name":"emails"}]},{"content":[{"anchor":"discussion","type":"heading","text":"Discussion","level":2},{"inlineContent":[{"text":"Convenience method that combines ","type":"text"},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"setUserId:"},{"type":"text","text":" and "},{"code":"setEmails:","type":"codeVoice"},{"text":" into a single","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"server request. This is more efficient than calling both methods separately","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"and ensures atomic association of user ID with emails."}],"type":"paragraph"},{"inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"Use this during login or registration flows when you have both user ID"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"and email available simultaneously.","type":"text"}],"type":"paragraph"},{"anchor":"Example","level":2,"text":"Example","type":"heading"},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"Complete registration with user ID and emails:"}]},{"syntax":"swift","code":["class RegistrationManager {","","    func completeRegistration(_ registration: RegistrationData) {","        \/\/ Create user on backend","        APIClient.shared.createUser(registration) { result in","            guard case .success(let user) = result else { return }","","            \/\/ Set both user ID and emails in single operation","            var emails = [user.email]","            if let secondaryEmail = registration.secondaryEmail {","                emails.append(secondaryEmail)","            }","","            Pushwoosh.configure.setUser(user.id, emails: emails)","","            \/\/ Set initial user tags","            Pushwoosh.configure.setTags([","                \"registration_date\": ISO8601DateFormatter().string(from: Date()),","                \"registration_source\": registration.source.rawValue,","                \"account_type\": user.accountType.rawValue,","                \"has_completed_onboarding\": false","            ])","        }","    }","}"],"type":"codeListing"},{"code":["   when you need confirmation."],"type":"codeListing","syntax":null}],"kind":"content"}],"sections":[],"identifier":{"interfaceLanguage":"occ","url":"doc:\/\/com.pushwoosh.PushwooshCore\/documentation\/PushwooshCore\/PWConfiguration\/setUser:emails:"},"kind":"symbol","hierarchy":{"paths":[["d